cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on developing controls for an Autonomous Surface Vehicle (ASV) to navigate in dynamic marine environments. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The ASV is equipped with bathymetric and water quality monitoring sensors, which may involve computer vision techniques for data processing and analysis. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes novel methods for sensing and controlling external forces (currents and winds) to enable precise maneuvers of the ASV. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The ASV may use AI techniques for decision-making and path planning in dynamic environments. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software development for implementing the proposed control algorithms and integrating the sensing and monitoring sensors with the ASV.
